WEBVTT

00:02.125 --> 00:04.404
Josslyn Carver... Will you marry me?

00:04.429 --> 00:07.947
<i>- Yes! Yes!
- Previously on "Mistresses"...</i>

00:07.971 --> 00:10.527
- I like to live a certain way.
- Why me?

00:10.552 --> 00:12.608
You were just the easiest target, you know?

00:12.642 --> 00:14.799
[Engine revs]

00:15.555 --> 00:18.106
Karen: Anna's staying with
me. I don't know for how long.

00:18.131 --> 00:20.024
You have always led with your heart,

00:20.049 --> 00:21.651
and that's why I love you.

00:22.218 --> 00:24.186
April Malloy here to see agent Thomas.

00:24.220 --> 00:25.387
Do you have an appointment?

00:25.421 --> 00:28.390
I am here to find out why the FBI bugged

00:28.424 --> 00:30.058
my 12-year-old daughter's bedroom.

00:30.093 --> 00:31.694
Do I need an appointment for that?

00:33.429 --> 00:34.568
Daniel?

00:36.665 --> 00:37.799
Daniel?

00:37.833 --> 00:39.172
If we do that...

00:41.033 --> 00:43.305
What are you doing here?

00:43.339 --> 00:44.959
Um...

00:47.595 --> 00:49.116
Let's go into my office

00:49.141 --> 00:51.142
- so we can discuss this in private.
- Your office?

00:53.716 --> 00:55.229
April, um...

00:56.984 --> 00:58.652
I work for the FBI.

00:58.921 --> 01:00.423
[Exhales sharply]

01:01.286 --> 01:03.667
What? Are you telling me
this whole thing was a lie?

01:03.692 --> 01:05.358
How is that even possible?

01:05.382 --> 01:07.851
- I met you at an art show.
- You were brought there.

01:08.196 --> 01:09.830
No, I wasn't.

01:09.864 --> 01:12.704
I-I-I went with my girlfriends
and my friend Mickey.

01:15.979 --> 01:18.272
You used Mickey to get me there?

01:18.306 --> 01:20.659
- It wasn't...
- As I told you the other day,

01:20.684 --> 01:22.285
this is an extremely important case.

01:22.310 --> 01:23.443
Yeah, I got that.

01:23.711 --> 01:24.711
April...

01:24.746 --> 01:26.509
if you wanted information about Paul,

01:26.534 --> 01:28.167
why didn't you just come
to me in the first place?!

01:28.192 --> 01:29.878
Why would you go through all this trouble

01:29.903 --> 01:31.141
just to humiliate me?!

01:31.166 --> 01:32.633
Thomas: You already lied
to the authorities once

01:32.658 --> 01:33.691
to protect your husband.

01:34.121 --> 01:35.288
We didn't know if we could trust you.

01:35.322 --> 01:36.989
<i>Trust me?</i>

01:37.131 --> 01:38.599
That's funny.

01:38.993 --> 01:42.676
This whole thing... [Sighs]

01:43.183 --> 01:45.417
Oh. [Scoffs] I... I don't believe this.

01:45.442 --> 01:47.033
I never meant for you to find out this way.

01:47.068 --> 01:48.845
- If you'd just let me explain...
- Explain what?

01:48.870 --> 01:51.560
That this whole thing was a lie?!

01:51.585 --> 01:54.537
Look, all that matters now
is where we go from here.

01:54.562 --> 01:56.283
All that matters to you, maybe.

01:57.311 --> 01:58.343
April.

02:03.732 --> 02:06.367
<font color="#ffff00">Captions by vitac</font>
Sync and corrections by Albanda
www.Addic7ed.com

02:06.392 --> 02:09.229
What about a receptionist for a P.R. firm?

02:09.255 --> 02:10.723
That might be interesting.

02:10.776 --> 02:13.278
Maybe, if they didn't
require a college degree.

02:13.303 --> 02:15.536
All the decent listings require a degree.

02:15.861 --> 02:18.095
How did the apartment hunting go yesterday?

02:18.120 --> 02:20.700
I went to a few. Nothing great.

02:21.131 --> 02:24.301
I saw some of them online.
Didn't look that bad.

02:25.017 --> 02:26.540
They're not.

02:27.404 --> 02:30.869
But with the security deposit
and the first month down,

02:31.043 --> 02:34.394
the fact is I don't have enough
money for anything decent,

02:34.419 --> 02:37.604
and I can't realistically
stay on your couch forever.

02:38.392 --> 02:41.663
[Sighs] It all feels like a huge dead end.

02:41.721 --> 02:43.653
I wish I could just go home.

02:43.789 --> 02:45.423
Anna, we discussed this.

02:45.457 --> 02:46.992
Your apartment isn't safe enough.

02:47.026 --> 02:49.106
I meant home to Korea.

02:49.694 --> 02:50.733
Oh.

02:51.931 --> 02:54.499
I didn't realize that was
something you were considering.

02:54.799 --> 02:58.921
It's not. I mean, how could I?

02:59.304 --> 03:00.861
That would mean telling my parents

03:00.886 --> 03:03.021
I've been lying to them for years.

03:03.415 --> 03:07.818
They think I'm married
and happy and successful.

03:08.491 --> 03:12.548
Maybe if you gave them a
chance, they might surprise you.

03:12.573 --> 03:14.640
Or they might reject me.

03:16.587 --> 03:17.855
Sorry. I'm sorry...

03:17.889 --> 03:19.356
- [Chuckles]
- [Laughs]

03:19.390 --> 03:21.119
For being such a pain in the ass.

03:21.144 --> 03:23.200
Seriously, I'm so grateful to you.

03:23.327 --> 03:26.796
No one's ever shown
this much interest in me.

03:26.830 --> 03:27.964
[Chuckles]

03:27.998 --> 03:31.535
[Chuckles]

03:36.440 --> 03:38.080
She's not here.

03:38.441 --> 03:39.862
Yeah, I can see that.

03:40.010 --> 03:41.510
I'm heading out to lunch.

03:41.545 --> 03:44.224
Do you... Need something from me?

03:45.054 --> 03:46.662
Just enjoying the view.

03:46.687 --> 03:47.988
[Chuckles]

03:48.013 --> 03:49.313
Got to say, you, uh...

03:50.518 --> 03:52.021
You look like a million bucks.

03:52.454 --> 03:53.887
[Cellphone ringing]

03:57.394 --> 03:58.694
Jim, hey.

03:58.728 --> 04:00.696
Thanks for getting back to me so quickly.

04:00.730 --> 04:02.423
Yeah, listen, I, um...

04:03.733 --> 04:06.368
I wanted to talk to you about
one of your former associates,

04:06.403 --> 04:08.204
Antonia Ruiz.

04:08.238 --> 04:11.111
Yeah, that's right. Toni.

04:12.202 --> 04:15.000
Are you sure it's over between you and Dom?

04:15.144 --> 04:18.603
It seemed like there was so
much good stuff between you.

04:18.981 --> 04:20.281
I know. I know.

04:20.315 --> 04:22.880
But all that got messed up along the way.

04:23.065 --> 04:25.024
And it seems like we tried,

04:25.049 --> 04:27.483
but there was just nowhere to go, you know?

04:28.479 --> 04:30.358
- I'm so sorry, sweetie.
- [Bell jingles]

04:30.392 --> 04:32.023
Guess who's getting married!

04:32.048 --> 04:34.282
And if you guessed me, you guessed right.

04:34.307 --> 04:35.589
- Oh, my God!
- Aah!

04:35.614 --> 04:38.003
- Married to who?
- [Gasps] What? To Scott.

04:38.028 --> 04:39.710
Who else would it be?
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

04:39.735 --> 04:41.402
Savi, why are you wearing the
depressed ponytail in here?

04:41.437 --> 04:42.468
What were you two just talking about?

04:42.493 --> 04:45.025
Savi and Dom broke up. Have I met Scott?

04:45.050 --> 04:46.518
Ohh. No. Are you okay?

04:46.543 --> 04:48.177
- It's okay.
- We can be sad about that later.

04:48.202 --> 04:50.574
Right now, I just want to freak out

04:50.599 --> 04:52.415
because my baby sister is getting married!

04:52.440 --> 04:53.814
Aah! [Laughs]

04:53.849 --> 04:54.949
Let me see the ring.

04:54.983 --> 04:56.884
- [Both gasp]
- I need to get it sized

04:56.918 --> 04:59.220
- 'cause it keeps falling off.
- Honey, it's beautiful.

04:59.245 --> 05:00.336
It is, isn't it?

05:00.361 --> 05:01.428
- Yeah!
- Oh, my God!

05:01.453 --> 05:02.820
- [Laughs]
- [Bell jingles]

05:02.923 --> 05:05.492
This is crazy! I'm so excited!

05:05.816 --> 05:07.700
Joss just told us she's getting married!

05:07.725 --> 05:09.759
But Savi and Dom are broken up.

05:09.930 --> 05:11.823
Daniel's an FBI agent.

05:11.932 --> 05:13.924
He was using me to get to Paul.

05:16.444 --> 05:18.497
I'm never playing this game with her again.

