05:31.368 --> 05:32.402
[Sighs]

05:32.436 --> 05:35.070
Hello? [Door opens]

05:35.105 --> 05:38.267
[Door closes] Hey. I have some big news.

05:38.292 --> 05:40.943
Yeah? So do I. Greta is psychotic.

05:41.655 --> 05:43.326
Oh, no. What happened?

05:43.351 --> 05:44.485
Look at this e-mail from her.

05:44.519 --> 05:46.420
We're three weeks out from the soft open.

05:46.454 --> 05:48.922
I was literally about to have
you send the menus to the printer.

05:48.956 --> 05:50.019
- Yeah?
- And she wants to throw out

05:50.019 --> 05:51.019
everything.

05:51.044 --> 05:53.320
Whoa, whoa, whoa. But she
already approved the menus.

05:53.345 --> 05:55.796
Exactly, and now she's not
sure it's ambitious enough.

05:55.821 --> 05:57.622
She's thinking... Ho ho ho, wait for it.

05:57.647 --> 05:58.961
- Huh?
- "Japanese-y."

05:58.961 --> 06:00.011
She literally used that word.

06:00.011 --> 06:01.837
And... and look at this. Only in L.A.

06:01.862 --> 06:05.481
Her psychic says "to avoid using
all white and purple vegetables

06:05.506 --> 06:08.474
- until at least the spring of 2015."
- Oh, well, okay.

06:08.509 --> 06:10.110
This is a lot of interesting information.

06:10.144 --> 06:11.607
There's nothing interesting about it, Joss.

06:11.632 --> 06:14.266
I'm not a short-order cook
for some whack-job model

06:14.291 --> 06:16.426
who doesn't know a lentil from a snap pea.

06:16.650 --> 06:19.017
You know what? I-I'd just rather
walk out before I get fired.

06:19.042 --> 06:21.121
Oh, my... Harry! Stop it.

06:21.221 --> 06:22.901
You're not gonna get fired, okay?

06:22.979 --> 06:25.157
You two just need to
sit down and talk it out.

06:25.182 --> 06:27.747
It's all a part of the process.
I've seen it a million times.

06:27.772 --> 06:29.561
Usually it's on some reality show.

06:29.595 --> 06:31.230
But I think... you think
that I'm being difficult?

06:31.264 --> 06:33.732
What?! Of course not.

06:33.766 --> 06:35.325
No, you're being you.

06:35.350 --> 06:36.945
You're an amazing chef. She's being Greta.

06:36.970 --> 06:38.569
She's difficult. What
do you want? I mean...

06:38.594 --> 06:40.032
But she needs you, Harry,

06:40.057 --> 06:42.391
<i>and I really need you.</i>

06:44.733 --> 06:46.819
- Fine.
- [Sighs] Thank you.

06:46.988 --> 06:49.323
Okay, now come here. Breathe.

06:49.348 --> 06:52.805
Let's just see what she's
really even asking us, okay?

06:53.619 --> 06:54.753
Sensible people.

06:54.787 --> 06:55.821
[Groans]

06:55.855 --> 06:57.823
Look, chiquino peppers
are so hot right now.

06:57.857 --> 06:59.324
- What's your big news?
- Hmm?

06:59.359 --> 07:00.694
Your big news.

07:00.950 --> 07:02.338
Oh! Oh.

07:02.363 --> 07:04.832
- You know what?
- I don't even remember anymore.

07:04.857 --> 07:06.324
Let's talk menu.

07:06.349 --> 07:08.818
Uh, "without any evil
white or purple vegetables."

07:08.843 --> 07:10.616
- What does that even... ?
- [Scoffs]

07:15.750 --> 07:17.218
You got a minute?

07:20.768 --> 07:22.451
It's about Toni.

07:22.748 --> 07:24.373
Take it to H.R.

07:24.398 --> 07:26.805
Look, I spoke to Jim
Fletcher, one of the partners

07:26.830 --> 07:28.451
at the last firm Toni worked for.

07:28.476 --> 07:30.843
I wanted to find out why Toni
left there after just a year.

07:30.868 --> 07:32.299
You know what he said?

07:32.777 --> 07:34.612
He said he didn't want to get into it,

07:34.637 --> 07:36.437
which means he couldn't get into it.

07:36.462 --> 07:38.167
I'm guessing something happened there, too.

07:38.192 --> 07:40.175
I don't know. And I don't care.

07:40.231 --> 07:41.926
What I do know is that you had sex with

07:41.951 --> 07:43.433
two associates at this firm.

07:43.467 --> 07:44.954
And if I were you,

07:44.979 --> 07:47.070
I'd be mighty grateful
that I still had a job here.

07:47.138 --> 07:48.601
- Mitchell.
- Keep your head down.

07:48.626 --> 07:51.261
Do your work. Stay away
from both of those women.

07:51.642 --> 07:52.742
Understand?

07:59.417 --> 08:02.051
[Sighs]

08:02.085 --> 08:05.170
What do you think... tie or... or no tie?

08:07.257 --> 08:09.058
You know, it would be a lot easier to help

08:09.092 --> 08:11.060
if I knew what this interview's about.

08:11.094 --> 08:13.332
Oh, I'm not... not telling.
Don't want to jinx it.

08:13.357 --> 08:15.158
You're nervous, aren't you?

08:15.289 --> 08:18.424
I haven't had a job
interview in over 10 years.

08:18.701 --> 08:21.170
- I'm not used to winning people over.
- [Chuckles]

08:21.204 --> 08:26.000
Really? You won me over the
first five minutes I met you.

08:26.774 --> 08:29.075
You have a natural way
of putting people at ease.

08:29.100 --> 08:31.542
That's why you're such a good therapist.

08:36.022 --> 08:38.486
I love when you do that.

08:38.520 --> 08:41.155
Hey, you, uh... You busy tonight?

08:41.190 --> 08:44.662
Dinner, movie, maybe... My place?

08:44.687 --> 08:49.649
I wish I could, but, um, I
can't leave Anna that long.

08:49.698 --> 08:51.511
Uh, definitely not overnight.

08:51.536 --> 08:54.605
You mean Anna your... your new roommate?

08:54.971 --> 08:56.821
I know. I know.

08:57.071 --> 08:59.606
But at this point, all
I want to do is help her.

08:59.875 --> 09:02.510
So, Anna told me she wants
to go back home to Korea,

09:02.544 --> 09:05.179
but she's afraid of how
her parents will react.

09:05.213 --> 09:07.515
I keep thinking of how
I'd tell her to handle it

09:07.549 --> 09:09.203
if we were still in session.

09:09.384 --> 09:11.508
But you're not in session anymore.

09:11.533 --> 09:13.000
I mean, for better or worse,

09:13.025 --> 09:15.166
your relationship's completely changed.

09:16.310 --> 09:19.158
Maybe you should think about
what you'd say to her as a friend.

09:26.167 --> 09:29.303
I've already started to call some venues,

09:29.337 --> 09:31.972
and shutters can see
you as early as Friday,

09:32.006 --> 09:33.640
if you want to go beachy
with the whole thing.

09:33.674 --> 09:35.876
God, you're officially gonna take
over this wedding, aren't you?

09:35.910 --> 09:37.544
Oh, yeah, just sit back

09:37.578 --> 09:41.047
and let my organizational
skills wash all over you.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.348
- [Laughs]
- Excuse me.

09:43.951 --> 09:44.985
Oh, thanks.

09:49.298 --> 09:50.974
Dude, that's not my car.

09:50.999 --> 09:52.900
[Chuckles]

09:54.290 --> 09:55.872
What is this?

09:55.897 --> 09:57.864
- "Joss, I can't wait to marry you."
- [Gasps]

09:57.889 --> 10:00.400
"You drive me insane. Drive safe.
Precious cargo. Love, Scott."

10:00.434 --> 10:01.552
What?

10:01.577 --> 10:03.513
Wait, wait, he bought...
he bought you this car?

10:03.537 --> 10:05.504
Oh, my God, he bought you this car?!

10:05.539 --> 10:06.877
Where's my car?

10:06.902 --> 10:08.737
Your fiancé drove it back home.

10:08.762 --> 10:10.162
Savi: Oh, my God!

10:17.699 --> 10:21.434
This is like being in the
cockpit of a private plane.

10:21.718 --> 10:23.009
[Sighs]

10:23.034 --> 10:24.802
You never told me Scott was loaded.

10:24.827 --> 10:26.518
Well, I never really thought about it.

10:26.559 --> 10:28.860
I guess we do go to nice restaurants,

10:28.894 --> 10:30.262
and his place is really great.

10:30.296 --> 10:33.088
Okay, you're the designated
driver from now on, okay?

10:35.468 --> 10:36.935
What's wrong?

10:36.969 --> 10:38.436
Hmm? Hmm?

10:38.470 --> 10:40.099
Oh, uh...

10:40.639 --> 10:43.441
Nothing, I just... I can't
believe this is my car.

10:43.475 --> 10:45.777
- [Laughs] Believe it.
- Hmm.

10:45.811 --> 10:47.018
Let's drive.

10:47.043 --> 10:49.512
[Laughing] Okay, Thelma. Calm down.

10:49.537 --> 10:51.991
Let me see if I can figure this sucker out.

10:52.952 --> 10:55.682
I mean... I think it's that thing.

10:55.707 --> 10:56.943
[Knock on door]

10:58.976 --> 11:00.757
All you have to do is hear me out.

11:08.276 --> 11:09.620
Are you even married?

11:09.934 --> 11:11.735
[Sighs] No.

11:11.769 --> 11:13.847
[Scoffs] Of course you're not.

11:13.940 --> 11:16.174
Even that was a lie. Everything was...

11:16.199 --> 11:17.661
No, not everything.

11:17.686 --> 11:19.517
- Oh, don't you dare.
- No, I loved you.

11:19.542 --> 11:20.666
I still love you.

11:20.691 --> 11:23.154
<i>No, you loved getting
information out of me.</i>

11:23.180 --> 11:24.447
It wasn't like that!

11:24.482 --> 11:26.116
Okay, yeah, I was sent to that art show

11:26.150 --> 11:27.783
to... to meet you and forge a relationship,

11:27.818 --> 11:29.700
but it... it was never
supposed to become...

11:29.778 --> 11:31.568
What? Sexual?

11:31.593 --> 11:34.262
[Sighs] I know I crossed the line.

11:36.054 --> 11:37.627
Were you supposed to get my little girl

11:37.661 --> 11:39.129
to fall in love with you, too?

11:39.163 --> 11:42.696
Don't say that. You know
how I feel about Lucy.

11:42.821 --> 11:44.299
Look, we'd been tracking Paul

11:44.334 --> 11:45.868
for over a year before we met, okay?

11:45.902 --> 11:48.037
And there were so many times
that I wanted to tell you.

11:48.071 --> 11:49.371
But you didn't!

11:49.405 --> 11:52.008
Because your job was so
much more important than me!

11:52.042 --> 11:54.935
No, it wasn't the job,
okay? It was the case.

11:55.378 --> 11:57.113
And I've been working on
it since the beginning,

11:57.147 --> 11:58.848
and there are some
serious criminals involved.

11:58.882 --> 12:01.016
And they're hurting good people every day.

12:01.050 --> 12:02.518
Look, it really doesn't matter.

12:02.552 --> 12:05.548
I don't care, and I'm
not doing this anymore.

12:05.821 --> 12:07.789
So you can tell agent Thomas I'm out.

12:07.823 --> 12:10.392
Find another way to get to Paul.

12:11.133 --> 12:13.028
It's not that simple.

12:13.062 --> 12:14.382
<i>It is that simple!</i>

12:14.664 --> 12:16.397
[Sighs]

12:16.431 --> 12:17.732
[Sighs]

12:17.767 --> 12:19.840
Now, can you please just leave my house

12:19.865 --> 12:21.699
and never come back?

12:23.222 --> 12:25.490
<i>Never come back, Daniel.</i>

12:29.683 --> 12:30.912
[Door opens]

12:32.439 --> 12:33.839
[Door closes]

12:50.304 --> 12:52.471
[Cellphone ringing]

12:54.500 --> 12:55.967
Zack. Hi.

12:56.001 --> 12:57.757
Savi, hey, I'm glad you picked up.

12:57.782 --> 12:59.824
Uh, did you ever get my message?

12:59.910 --> 13:00.915
I did.

13:00.940 --> 13:02.856
I was gonna call you back,

13:03.196 --> 13:05.164
and then I was gonna e-mail you back.

13:05.277 --> 13:08.624
And then I just chickened out completely.

13:09.753 --> 13:12.968
I just... I wasn't sure if you
were still mad at me or not.

13:13.118 --> 13:15.375
Oh, I was... I was never mad at you.

13:15.487 --> 13:19.364
So, uh, do you think we should
go back to being friends?

13:19.841 --> 13:21.736
Yeah. I'd like that.

13:22.627 --> 13:26.096
Hey, uh, before I forget,
did you ever wind up moving?

13:26.130 --> 13:30.033
No, I decided to keep my house. Why?

13:30.068 --> 13:32.169
So your address is still the same?

13:32.203 --> 13:34.647
Uh, yeah, h-ho... hold on one second.

13:34.784 --> 13:36.225
What is this?

13:36.670 --> 13:38.771
They just asked me to get your signatures.

13:43.714 --> 13:45.849
Uh, Zack, can I call you back?

13:45.883 --> 13:47.150
I'm at work right now.

13:47.185 --> 13:48.775
Yeah, no problem. We'll talk soon.

13:48.800 --> 13:50.290
Okay. Bye.

13:54.713 --> 13:57.035
Great. Coordinate with Davis.
He needs to be on the call.

13:57.060 --> 13:59.696
- Dom, can I talk to you for a second?
- Uh, not really.

13:59.730 --> 14:01.972
I just noticed I was taken
off the Breitling case.

14:01.997 --> 14:03.343
Yeah, well, you're gonna have
to take it up with Mitchell.

14:03.368 --> 14:04.734
Well, I'd rather take it up with you,

14:04.759 --> 14:06.711
<i>since you were there when
I was put on the case.</i>

14:06.736 --> 14:07.970
- [Sighs]
- Wait a minute.

14:08.005 --> 14:10.106
Are you seriously walking
away from me right now?

14:10.140 --> 14:12.975
I said take it up with Mitchell.
There's nothing more I can do.

14:13.010 --> 14:14.243
Look, I-I'm sorry, but I cannot be having

14:14.277 --> 14:16.057
this conversation with you right now.

14:16.082 --> 14:18.047
- Mitchell was very specific about us not...
- But...

14:18.072 --> 14:20.040
I don't want to be having this
conversation, either, okay?

14:20.065 --> 14:22.298
I really think we could
both use a little space.

14:22.323 --> 14:24.625
- Savi, I don't...
- But this is my job,

14:24.650 --> 14:27.145
and you can't just screw
me over on stuff like this

14:27.170 --> 14:28.419
just because you're mad at me.

14:28.444 --> 14:30.728
I'm the one who got you on
this case in the first place.

14:30.753 --> 14:32.656
So do me a favor... Stop complaining,

14:32.681 --> 14:34.648
or feel free to find a job someplace else.

14:44.076 --> 14:46.577
[Indistinct whispering]

14:54.319 --> 14:55.486
I'm seriously so embarrassed

14:55.520 --> 14:57.141
that I'm even bothering
you with any of this

14:57.166 --> 14:58.567
considering everything you're
going through with Daniel.

14:58.592 --> 15:00.271
- No, Daniel is over.
- [Sighs]

15:00.296 --> 15:02.708
And besides, I am so
happy for the distraction.

15:02.959 --> 15:04.760
So, what's the problem, okay?

15:04.785 --> 15:06.052
You had a fight with Scott?

15:06.447 --> 15:08.056
[Whimpers, sighs]

15:08.081 --> 15:09.186
Okay.

15:11.266 --> 15:12.967
He bought me a Tesla.

15:13.001 --> 15:14.801
I think we have different definitions

15:14.836 --> 15:15.857
of the word "problem."

15:15.882 --> 15:18.181
April, do you remember how excited I was

15:18.206 --> 15:19.306
when I bought my coupe?

15:19.341 --> 15:20.441
I saved every penny

15:20.475 --> 15:22.409
and I bargained my sweet little ass off

15:22.444 --> 15:24.344
to get the best deal
and it's finally paid off

15:24.518 --> 15:27.189
and it's cute and it's
dented and it sputters.

15:27.214 --> 15:29.039
But it's mine, and I love it.

15:29.122 --> 15:31.257
I could never, in a million
years, afford that Tesla.

15:31.385 --> 15:33.520
So Scott is making you pay
the payments on the car?

15:33.554 --> 15:35.698
No! That's the worst part.

15:35.723 --> 15:37.199
It's a gift... the gift of dependency.

15:37.224 --> 15:38.904
And you want to know the worst, worst part?

15:38.929 --> 15:40.202
I'm already getting used to it.

15:40.227 --> 15:42.228
What... it's okay to get
used to his lifestyle.

15:42.262 --> 15:44.130
You're marrying him. What's his is yours.

15:44.164 --> 15:45.631
[Sighs]

15:45.665 --> 15:46.866
Do you know what I always thought

15:46.900 --> 15:48.868
would be the hardest
part about marriage, hmm?

15:48.902 --> 15:50.136
Monogamy.

15:50.170 --> 15:52.438
- But you know what?
- I could sleep with only Scott

15:52.473 --> 15:54.573
for the rest of my life
and be totally fine.

15:54.608 --> 15:58.311
It's stuff like this crazy
Tesla thing that freaks me out.

15:58.345 --> 16:00.141
I've been a kept woman, April.

16:00.166 --> 16:02.700
- I can't do it again.
- Ah.

16:03.082 --> 16:06.184
Joss, this is not the same
as being someone's mistress.

16:06.219 --> 16:08.558
- Isn't it?!
- What kind of gift is that?!

16:08.583 --> 16:11.328
It completely throws the whole
balance of power out of whack!

16:11.388 --> 16:13.489
How am I ever supposed to get mad at him

16:13.514 --> 16:15.215
when he can hold a Tesla over my head?

16:15.423 --> 16:18.140
April, I've spent the last year
trying to get my life together,

16:18.165 --> 16:19.865
and I am finally the independent woman

16:19.890 --> 16:21.557
that Destiny's Child wanted me to be.

16:21.696 --> 16:23.162
- [Laughs]
- So tell me this...

16:23.197 --> 16:25.832
what if marrying Scott
changes all that, hmm?

16:27.024 --> 16:29.692
You're not considering calling
off the engagement, are you?

16:29.717 --> 16:32.520
I don't know. I don't want to lose Scott.

16:32.555 --> 16:34.336
But I don't want to lose myself.

16:36.289 --> 16:37.792
Hmm.

16:40.447 --> 16:42.000
I'm gonna ask my boss

16:42.025 --> 16:43.826
about picking up more shifts at the diner

16:43.851 --> 16:45.472
so I'm not in your hair so much.

16:45.497 --> 16:47.664
You're not in my hair at all.

16:51.448 --> 16:54.892
I was actually hoping we could
discuss this idea of yours

16:54.917 --> 16:57.348
about going back to Korea a little more.

16:57.410 --> 16:59.377
Ugh, I never should have brought that up.

16:59.452 --> 17:00.897
I'm glad you did.

17:00.922 --> 17:02.991
It gave me a lot to think about.

17:04.833 --> 17:07.367
Do you know why I wanted
to become a psychiatrist?

17:07.839 --> 17:10.541
You had a temporary lapse in sanity?

17:10.576 --> 17:12.544
No. [Chuckles]

17:12.578 --> 17:14.276
It was because of my parents.

17:14.965 --> 17:16.666
They wanted you to be a doctor.

17:16.692 --> 17:18.892
Or a lawyer. As long as it was successful.

17:18.916 --> 17:20.683
That's all that mattered to my mother.

17:20.752 --> 17:22.837
I felt like she was
always hovering around me,

17:22.862 --> 17:26.319
always pushing me, but never seeing me.

17:26.701 --> 17:29.670
Most of the time, I was lonely.

17:32.264 --> 17:35.930
As I was growing up, I
wanted to connect with people.

17:35.955 --> 17:39.079
I wanted to be meaningful in a way

17:39.104 --> 17:41.279
that I didn't feel with my own family.

17:42.207 --> 17:44.575
And I thought becoming a psychiatrist

17:44.609 --> 17:46.093
would help me achieve that.

17:46.118 --> 17:49.246
So I applied to every
school on the west coast.

17:49.348 --> 17:52.927
I wanted to get as far
away as I could. [Chuckles]

17:53.047 --> 17:54.781
And you got into Stanford.

17:54.806 --> 17:56.973
Oh, my mother was over the moon.

17:57.321 --> 17:58.856
It never occurred to her

17:58.890 --> 18:01.745
that she wouldn't be seeing
me more than once a year.

18:02.040 --> 18:04.280
But we didn't have much money,

18:04.305 --> 18:07.146
and flights to New York
were very expensive.

18:07.738 --> 18:09.544
As time went on,

18:09.992 --> 18:12.471
I wound up visiting less and less.

18:13.105 --> 18:17.046
I kept thinking to myself,
"I'll go next Christmas.

18:17.492 --> 18:19.392
I'll go next summer."

18:19.810 --> 18:22.684
Then one day, I got a call from my father

18:22.709 --> 18:25.711
that my... mother had passed away.

18:28.419 --> 18:29.537
[Chuckles]

18:29.893 --> 18:32.462
I'd finally become this successful woman

18:32.487 --> 18:34.455
she'd always wanted me to be,

18:34.608 --> 18:37.443
and she never got a chance to see it.

18:41.043 --> 18:44.365
[Voice breaking] And I never
got a chance to say goodbye.

18:45.235 --> 18:47.564
Why didn't you tell me any of this before?

18:47.904 --> 18:50.881
Well, our sessions were about you.

18:51.984 --> 18:53.764
But we're friends now.

18:54.244 --> 18:59.123
As my friend, I wanted you to know this

19:00.156 --> 19:03.032
because I don't want the
same to happen to you.

19:11.527 --> 19:14.029
Always fireworks with you two, huh?

19:15.404 --> 19:17.205
Should I leave you alone for a minute?

19:17.317 --> 19:19.091
Uh, no.

19:19.257 --> 19:22.125
No, it's fine. I'm... I'm okay. Thank you.

19:22.573 --> 19:23.874
Look, it's none of my business,

19:23.899 --> 19:26.200
but if I were you, I would
be reporting that crap.

19:26.225 --> 19:28.359
Yeah, you're right... it
is none of your business.

19:28.384 --> 19:32.020
He just humiliated you in
front of the entire office.

19:32.045 --> 19:33.746
Everyone knows you were screwing.

19:33.779 --> 19:36.427
Sounds like a hostile
work environment to me.

19:36.649 --> 19:38.302
Filing a fake harassment suit

19:38.327 --> 19:39.963
doesn't get you anywhere, okay?

19:39.988 --> 19:41.509
It's not gonna give me a leg up,

19:41.534 --> 19:43.708
and it's certainly not
gonna help me make partner.

19:43.845 --> 19:44.978
You know why?

19:45.028 --> 19:47.781
Because that's not how a
boys' club actually works.

19:49.309 --> 19:52.255
There are easier ways to make money.

19:52.922 --> 19:54.516
All you have to say is Dom made you

19:54.535 --> 19:57.268
feel uncomfortable after your
sexual relationship ended.

19:57.293 --> 19:59.728
Yeah, but he didn't make
me feel uncomfortable.

20:00.108 --> 20:02.375
Me, either, but that doesn't matter.

20:02.410 --> 20:05.044
All you have to do is
establish a pattern of behavior.

20:05.079 --> 20:06.454
The rest will take care of itself.

20:06.788 --> 20:10.757
Wow. You really are a horrible person.

20:10.818 --> 20:12.018
Sleep on it.

20:12.052 --> 20:13.855
Rich will look really good on you.

20:16.189 --> 20:17.790
Hmm.

20:25.021 --> 20:29.890
♪ Right, my little pooh
bear, want to take a chance? ♪

20:29.915 --> 20:33.218
♪ Want to sip this
smooth air, kick it ♪

20:33.253 --> 20:34.886
Did you bring the new menus?

20:34.920 --> 20:36.121
[Chuckles]

20:36.155 --> 20:38.322
Greta, I'm happy to
discuss the menu with you,

20:38.357 --> 20:40.387
but I have not made any changes yet.

20:40.412 --> 20:41.879
Why not? We are on a deadline.

20:41.962 --> 20:43.818
Yep, I'm aware of the deadline, thank you.

20:43.843 --> 20:45.363
Uh, but I don't think
rushing through changes

20:45.397 --> 20:48.200
without thinking them
through is wise at this point.

20:48.225 --> 20:49.725
We've both got a lot riding on this.

20:50.946 --> 20:52.444
What are you suggesting?

20:53.763 --> 20:54.930
If we're gonna make this work,

20:54.965 --> 20:56.364
we have to find a way to compromise.

20:58.695 --> 21:01.409
[Laughing] You don't strike me as a guy

21:01.434 --> 21:03.116
who's used to compromising, Harry.

21:03.141 --> 21:05.775
No, I'm definitely not...
not when it comes to my food,

21:05.800 --> 21:09.559
but I'm willing to give
it a try if you are.

21:11.742 --> 21:13.743
I'll try anything once.

21:15.808 --> 21:18.010
Maybe even twice.

21:27.593 --> 21:29.627
[Indistinct conversations]

21:32.642 --> 21:34.276
Guess who got the new job.

21:34.301 --> 21:36.144
[Gasps] You're kidding!

21:36.169 --> 21:39.338
That's so great! I'm so happy for you!

21:39.519 --> 21:41.654
Now, do I finally get
to know what the job is?

21:41.679 --> 21:42.712
[Laughing] Yeah.

21:42.737 --> 21:44.370
So, uh, you know the studies

21:44.395 --> 21:46.695
I've been doing at UCLA
on addiction therapy?

21:46.720 --> 21:49.022
Well, an extended
fellowship just got funded,

21:49.047 --> 21:52.671
and they want me to
oversee the entire thing.

21:53.268 --> 21:56.282
Oh, my God, Jacob. [Sighs] That's amazing.

21:56.307 --> 21:58.942
Yeah, it also includes a
faculty teaching position

21:58.967 --> 22:01.628
and a chance to work with
patients at Boston Medical.

22:02.403 --> 22:03.419
Boston?

22:03.444 --> 22:05.079
Yeah, the funding came from B.U.,

22:05.104 --> 22:07.639
so they want the fellowship
to be based at the university.

22:07.985 --> 22:11.657
- That's an incredible opportunity.
- It is. It is.

22:11.731 --> 22:15.032
And, uh, you know what would
make it even more... amazing?

22:15.097 --> 22:16.397
If you came with me.

22:17.307 --> 22:19.047
To Boston?

22:19.072 --> 22:21.673
Look, I-I know it sounds crazy, but...

22:21.698 --> 22:24.705
You could practice there
just as easily as L.A.

22:25.124 --> 22:27.725
It would be a huge adventure, Karen.

22:28.189 --> 22:31.425
Perfect opportunity for
us both to start fresh,

22:31.450 --> 22:33.150
something new.

22:34.924 --> 22:38.843
I-I know it's, uh...
it's a lot to take in.

22:38.868 --> 22:41.937
Just... Just think about it, okay?

22:42.120 --> 22:43.787
No pressure. [Chuckles]

22:46.235 --> 22:48.103
[Sighs]

22:54.130 --> 22:55.130
[Bell jingles]

22:56.149 --> 22:57.783
Thomas: Hi, April.

22:58.465 --> 23:00.599
I was just about to close up for the day.

23:00.624 --> 23:02.891
Hmm, no problem. This
will only take a second.

23:02.916 --> 23:04.450
I'm sorry, but I'm actually late

23:04.475 --> 23:05.755
for an appointment with vendors.

23:05.780 --> 23:07.213
Actually, it's not a request.

23:07.422 --> 23:08.856
We have a problem.

23:09.008 --> 23:10.408
We hear you're not interested

23:10.433 --> 23:11.900
in cooperating with us anymore.

23:11.984 --> 23:13.385
That's correct.

23:13.410 --> 23:15.377
And I think that's pretty understandable,

23:15.402 --> 23:16.702
considering everything.

23:16.727 --> 23:18.929
Mm-hmm. Well, I'm sorry for your troubles.

23:19.150 --> 23:21.581
But I think you may have misunderstood.

23:21.606 --> 23:23.140
You don't really have a choice here.

23:23.165 --> 23:24.357
What if I refuse?

23:24.382 --> 23:25.582
First, we'd be forced

23:25.607 --> 23:28.074
to seize your bank
account and all your assets

23:28.099 --> 23:29.733
until the government gets reimbursed

23:29.758 --> 23:31.224
for the insurance money you received

23:31.249 --> 23:32.811
from your not-deceased husband.

23:32.836 --> 23:34.771
The fact is you knowingly participated

23:34.796 --> 23:36.547
in defrauding the United States government

23:36.572 --> 23:38.907
will probably result in
some jail time, as well.

23:39.026 --> 23:40.592
Then we'd want to talk to your daughter,

23:40.846 --> 23:42.947
find out what she knows about Paul.

23:43.153 --> 23:46.422
Who knows? Maybe she's had some
conversations with her father.

23:49.593 --> 23:52.061
Can we assume now that
when Paul contacts you,

23:52.096 --> 23:53.129
you'll let us know?

23:58.919 --> 24:01.709
Great. Have a nice evening.

24:03.162 --> 24:04.400
[Bell jingles]

24:07.462 --> 24:08.558
- Hey.
- Oh, hey!

24:08.583 --> 24:10.552
Babe, we need to talk about
where we're gonna go for dinner.

24:10.577 --> 24:11.844
Because I'm starving.

24:11.869 --> 24:13.803
Okay, but we need to talk
about something important first.

24:13.958 --> 24:15.591
What could be more important than Sushi?

24:15.885 --> 24:17.131
Indian?

24:17.156 --> 24:18.122
I could do thai food.

24:18.147 --> 24:19.380
What are you doing tomorrow morning?

24:19.482 --> 24:21.516
Is Tuesday consultation or surgeries?

24:21.957 --> 24:23.591
It's, uh, consultations, but
I can carve out an hour or two.

24:23.626 --> 24:24.692
Why? What's up?

24:24.727 --> 24:26.077
[Exhales sharply]

24:28.297 --> 24:30.297
[Dog barks in distance]

24:34.240 --> 24:36.704
So, um, I was thinking

24:36.739 --> 24:38.317
that maybe we could see a lawyer...

24:38.681 --> 24:39.847
About a prenup.

24:43.045 --> 24:45.646
Babe... and I'm gonna say this
in the nicest possible way,

24:45.671 --> 24:47.504
but you're broke.

24:48.487 --> 24:50.179
Okay. [Chuckles]

24:50.204 --> 24:53.172
First of all, um, I'm
definitely not broke, trust me.

24:53.197 --> 24:55.171
I've been broke before. I know broke.

24:55.171 --> 24:57.525
You're right. That came out
wrong, okay? And I'm sorry.

24:57.559 --> 25:00.407
Um, what I meant was... Just...

25:00.432 --> 25:02.186
Tell you what, why
don't you walk me through

25:02.211 --> 25:03.511
- what's going on in there?
- Okay.

25:03.536 --> 25:04.902
I just think that

25:04.927 --> 25:07.632
we need to figure out what
separates us as individuals

25:07.657 --> 25:11.744
before we go into this huge
partnership together, right?

25:11.769 --> 25:13.337
Money's a part of it,
but it's more than that.

25:13.362 --> 25:14.918
Why are you talking like this? I've
never heard you talk like this before.

25:14.943 --> 25:16.342
Because I've never really
thought about it before.

25:16.377 --> 25:17.735
And now I'm thinking about everything,

25:17.760 --> 25:19.527
and this is the one
thing that keeps coming up

25:19.552 --> 25:21.040
is I-I just... I don't know

25:21.065 --> 25:23.532
if I'm gonna be okay losing my independence

25:23.557 --> 25:25.725
once I become Mrs. Josslyn Carver.

25:27.304 --> 25:29.604
Oh, no, the "Mrs." is a huge concession.

25:29.629 --> 25:31.735
Last names are a deal breaker.
It's going in the prenup.

25:31.858 --> 25:33.993
Okay, well, I've had a
really long day, babe.

25:34.027 --> 25:36.361
- I don't understand what's happening.
- Of course you don't.

25:36.396 --> 25:37.863
Nothing changes for
you when we get married.

25:37.898 --> 25:39.031
But for me, it does.

25:39.066 --> 25:40.683
- Well, I don't see how.
- Okay.

25:40.708 --> 25:42.509
So let's just pretend

25:42.534 --> 25:44.167
that the credit-card
bills start rolling in,

25:44.192 --> 25:46.160
and then you just think it's easier

25:46.185 --> 25:48.322
to pay them through your
business manager or whatever,

25:48.347 --> 25:50.063
and you don't mention anything to me.

25:50.088 --> 25:52.377
In fact, you stop mentioning
things to me altogether,

25:52.402 --> 25:54.843
and, you know, I just forget

25:54.880 --> 25:56.337
how to do the most basic of things, right?

25:56.362 --> 25:57.390
Does that make sense?

25:57.415 --> 25:59.609
- Since when do I have a business manager?
- Or you die.

25:59.634 --> 26:01.641
Or you leave me and the
electricity gets turned off

26:01.666 --> 26:02.933
because I forget to pay the bills.

26:02.958 --> 26:04.192
And suddenly, I go into arrears.

26:04.217 --> 26:06.709
I don't even know what arrears
means, but it sounds terrible.

26:06.734 --> 26:09.173
I'm pretty sure I understand what's
going on here, and I get your point,

26:09.198 --> 26:11.336
but I think you're missing
the bigger point, which is...

26:11.361 --> 26:13.362
The fact that I actually
want to take care of you.

26:13.833 --> 26:16.968
Oh, my God! You are so not listening to me!

26:17.003 --> 26:18.703
That's not the point at all!

26:18.738 --> 26:20.318
- Is this about the car?
- No!

26:20.343 --> 26:23.611
This is... okay, I just think

26:23.636 --> 26:25.403
that it would be safer if we got a prenup.

26:25.428 --> 26:26.961
That way, if this doesn't work out,

26:26.986 --> 26:28.553
there's no confusion, okay?

26:31.483 --> 26:32.939
Well, that's not gonna happen.

26:32.964 --> 26:34.683
I'm not entering into a marriage with you

26:34.708 --> 26:35.808
preparing for failure, okay?

26:35.833 --> 26:37.213
That's not how my family does things.

26:37.238 --> 26:38.651
That's not how I do things.

26:39.291 --> 26:42.030
I love you, and I want to marry you.

26:42.440 --> 26:43.540
Marriage is sacred.

26:43.565 --> 26:44.865
It's something I plan
on doing just one time.

26:44.890 --> 26:46.958
So you're either in this with me 100%,

26:47.331 --> 26:48.736
or you're not.

26:52.037 --> 26:54.736
[Sighs]

26:57.642 --> 26:59.590
I'm not sure I can do this.

27:00.144 --> 27:02.112
Do you want me to talk to them first?

27:02.137 --> 27:03.537
Would that make it easier?

27:06.636 --> 27:08.555
Do your parents speak English?

27:08.886 --> 27:10.935
A little. Mostly my mom.

27:11.926 --> 27:14.027
Okay. Are you ready?

27:20.203 --> 27:22.604
Hello? Mrs. Choi?

27:22.800 --> 27:24.433
This is Dr. Kim.

27:24.467 --> 27:26.602
I'm a psychiatrist in Los Angeles

27:26.636 --> 27:28.838
who's been working with
your daughter, Anna.

27:28.872 --> 27:32.508
No, she's fine. She's sitting with me now.

27:32.542 --> 27:35.996
There's some things Anna
would like to discuss with you

27:36.021 --> 27:37.654
if you're open to that.

27:38.682 --> 27:40.385
Is now a good time?

27:41.784 --> 27:42.951
Hold on.

27:43.516 --> 27:45.813
Your mother wants to speak to you.

27:46.936 --> 27:48.757
You can do this.

27:55.431 --> 27:57.933
[Speaking Korean]

27:59.836 --> 28:02.838
[Sniffles]

28:22.199 --> 28:25.292
Molly: Sorry to interrupt. They're
asking for you in the conference room.

28:25.463 --> 28:27.228
Is this about the Bernardo case?

28:27.461 --> 28:28.868
No clue.

28:37.372 --> 28:40.173
Well, this is exciting.

28:41.360 --> 28:43.676
<i>Savi: Yeah, but he didn't
make me feel uncomfortable.</i>

28:43.710 --> 28:45.911
<i>Antonia: Me, either,
but that doesn't matter.</i>

28:45.945 --> 28:48.414
<i>All you have to do is
establish a pattern of behavior.</i>

28:48.448 --> 28:50.082
<i>The rest will take care of itself.</i>

28:53.118 --> 28:56.522
Anything you want to add to that, Toni?

29:19.924 --> 29:21.491
[Whistles]

29:21.525 --> 29:23.160
Baby, I'm not sure I can
have you leaving the house

29:23.194 --> 29:24.394
looking that gorgeous.

29:24.428 --> 29:26.563
Mm, thank you.

29:26.597 --> 29:28.731
I'm meeting the girls for lunch,
and then I have a few errands,

29:28.765 --> 29:30.400
and I have to see Greta
at the restaurant later,

29:30.434 --> 29:32.766
so I'm not sure what time I'll
be home, but I will text you.

29:32.791 --> 29:34.737
Okay. You got five minutes
to discuss something?

29:34.771 --> 29:36.406
Mm, I'm really running behind.

29:36.440 --> 29:37.973
I'm ready to do that prenup,

29:38.008 --> 29:39.942
but only if we can do it right now.

29:40.063 --> 29:43.228
- Hmm?
- Our version of a prenup, okay?

29:43.253 --> 29:48.059
No lawyers, no crap about
money, just non-negotiables.

29:48.084 --> 29:49.217
While you stand there mostly naked.

29:49.352 --> 29:51.253
I mean, you said you were in a hurry, so...

29:51.287 --> 29:52.666
Okay, first of all,

29:52.691 --> 29:55.159
this relationship shall be
equal and all-inclusive, okay?

29:55.184 --> 29:57.319
No one's gonna have all
the power, all the control.

29:57.460 --> 29:59.528
Everything that makes
you unique and individual

29:59.562 --> 30:00.995
shall be maintained, okay?

30:01.030 --> 30:02.188
Secondly...

30:04.033 --> 30:05.667
And this is really important to me...

30:05.702 --> 30:07.810
I'm not gonna pay all your bills, okay?

30:07.835 --> 30:09.168
So which bills... [Chuckles]

30:09.193 --> 30:10.884
Which bills are you interested in paying?

30:10.973 --> 30:14.207
Oh, you're se... Um, okay, phone and cable.

30:14.232 --> 30:16.177
Okay... and cable.

30:16.212 --> 30:19.470
So from now until the day that we die,

30:19.915 --> 30:23.184
Joss shall pay the phone and cable bill.

30:23.219 --> 30:25.553
- You want water and power, as well?
- Oh, no, thank you.

30:25.587 --> 30:28.116
I've seen how reckless you
are with your sprinklers.

30:29.424 --> 30:31.630
Which brings us to last names.

30:31.655 --> 30:33.370
I'm gonna keep my last name.

30:33.395 --> 30:34.695
- Hmm.
- Now, you get to keep yours.

30:34.730 --> 30:36.364
- Babies... well, they get both.
- Babies?

30:36.398 --> 30:37.898
Plural?

30:37.932 --> 30:39.800
Okay, well, I was thinking one.

30:39.834 --> 30:40.801
I was thinking four.

30:40.835 --> 30:42.403
- Two.
- Done.

30:42.807 --> 30:44.472
Is there anything else you want?

30:44.506 --> 30:46.474
- Yeah. You.
- Twice a week. Guaranteed.

30:46.508 --> 30:47.808
I'm not moving on that one.

30:47.842 --> 30:50.144
Are you out of your freaking mind?

30:50.178 --> 30:51.347
Give me that.

30:51.846 --> 30:54.990
<i>Sex at least five times a week,</i>

30:55.015 --> 30:57.815
and always at least once on weekends.

30:58.186 --> 30:59.887
[Pen scratches] A girl has needs.

30:59.921 --> 31:02.923
You... Drive a hard bargain.
I'm glad we cleared that up.

31:02.957 --> 31:04.157
[Chuckles]

31:06.026 --> 31:07.994
And no matter how old we get,

31:08.028 --> 31:10.797
you have to tell me you
love me at least once a day.

31:12.767 --> 31:14.734
- That part's easy.
- [Chuckles]

31:14.769 --> 31:16.436
Mmm.

31:21.574 --> 31:23.375
[Knock on door]

31:23.410 --> 31:25.211
Looks like our little plan worked.

31:25.245 --> 31:27.847
I never realized you
were such a good actor.

31:27.881 --> 31:30.950
All that yelling... You
scared the crap out of me.

31:30.984 --> 31:32.084
[Chuckles]

31:32.119 --> 31:34.586
Listen, um, thanks for
helping me with this.

31:34.621 --> 31:35.955
You didn't have to.

31:35.989 --> 31:37.523
Yeah, I did.

31:37.557 --> 31:39.191
Even though we're not together,

31:39.225 --> 31:40.759
I'll always have your back.

31:41.941 --> 31:43.929
And I will always have yours.

31:45.264 --> 31:48.434
So, has Mitchell decided
what he's gonna do yet?

31:48.468 --> 31:49.735
He said it's my call.

31:49.769 --> 31:52.771
Whatever I decide, the rest
of the partners will back me.

31:53.587 --> 31:59.011
Well, I am proud of
you, fancy-pants partner.

32:08.020 --> 32:10.321
Putting Anna on the plane was so intense,

32:10.356 --> 32:12.390
but I felt [chuckles] calm.

32:12.424 --> 32:14.058
Then when I was driving home...

32:14.092 --> 32:17.094
and suddenly, I just broke into tears.

32:17.128 --> 32:20.164
- Ohh, honey.
- I'm so happy for her,

32:20.198 --> 32:21.666
but it made me feel really sad

32:21.700 --> 32:24.105
for what I lost with my own mother.

32:25.371 --> 32:27.504
[Sighs] My whole family, really.

32:27.538 --> 32:31.175
I-it's silly, I know.
It's been so long now.

32:31.209 --> 32:33.244
Joss: No, there's nothing silly about it.

32:33.278 --> 32:34.725
That girl was lucky to have you, honey.

32:34.750 --> 32:36.688
You changed her life forever.

32:36.713 --> 32:37.880
She changed mine.

32:38.049 --> 32:39.250
For the first time, I felt like

32:39.284 --> 32:41.692
I made a real difference
in a patient's life.

32:41.853 --> 32:45.822
But I had to break every rule
of my profession to do it,

32:45.857 --> 32:47.888
which made me realize...

32:48.359 --> 32:50.927
I don't think this is the
right profession for me,

32:50.961 --> 32:52.095
not anymore.

32:52.129 --> 32:54.464
So I decided to quit.

32:55.065 --> 32:56.933
- What?
- What do you mean, "quit"?

32:56.967 --> 32:59.502
I mean, I'm not gonna be
a psychiatrist anymore.

32:59.536 --> 33:01.704
So, uh, what are you gonna do instead?

33:01.738 --> 33:03.482
I honestly have no idea.

33:04.241 --> 33:07.725
But Jacob asked me to
move to Boston with him.

33:07.750 --> 33:08.811
- What?!
- Boston?!

33:08.845 --> 33:09.979
I'm so confused. Where are we?

33:10.014 --> 33:10.980
I-I know. I know.

33:11.015 --> 33:13.116
It's a lot. It's a lot.

33:13.150 --> 33:14.217
"A lot" is putting it mildly.

33:14.251 --> 33:15.451
Savi: And that's kind of a big step

33:15.485 --> 33:17.319
for two people that aren't even dating.

33:17.353 --> 33:19.228
Actually, we have been dating.

33:19.689 --> 33:22.458
We just... Didn't tell people yet.

33:22.492 --> 33:25.007
April: Okay, it does
sound crazy and impulsive,

33:25.361 --> 33:27.195
but really romantic, too.

33:27.230 --> 33:28.531
I think you should do it.

33:28.565 --> 33:31.734
You do? I don't. I like you here.

33:31.768 --> 33:33.701
Well, I'm on board with
whatever you want to do,

33:33.736 --> 33:35.237
but you better be at my wedding, woman.

33:35.271 --> 33:37.613
Savi: Yeah, yeah. And...
and the bridal shower

33:37.638 --> 33:39.706
and all those other parties
I'm throwing my sister.

33:40.109 --> 33:41.676
[Laughs] And Lucy is going

33:41.710 --> 33:43.078
to insist you're here
for Christmas, obviously.

33:43.112 --> 33:44.579
You guys are freaking me out.

33:44.613 --> 33:46.401
I haven't even made up my mind yet.

33:46.426 --> 33:48.794
Whatever you decide to
do, we will make it work.

33:49.184 --> 33:50.852
Like we always do.

33:58.383 --> 34:00.485
- Yo.
- Yo.

34:00.510 --> 34:03.340
So, I just had a meeting with Greta,

34:03.365 --> 34:06.067
who is apparently back to
being thrilled with you.

34:06.101 --> 34:08.775
Gloating is not an
attractive look on you, Joss.

34:08.801 --> 34:12.091
Please! I noticed you saved
your date-and-mint-crusted lamb.

34:12.116 --> 34:13.583
Yeah, but lost my Sambuca prawns.

34:13.741 --> 34:15.609
Harry, consider it a big win.

34:15.643 --> 34:17.610
You managed to salvage 3/4 of that menu,

34:17.645 --> 34:20.281
which means I don't have to
re-conceive our entire concept

34:20.315 --> 34:22.783
or the table decorations or the invites.

34:22.817 --> 34:25.284
And "Japanese-y" definitely
did not make the cut.

34:25.319 --> 34:27.120
Oh, thank God.

34:27.154 --> 34:30.190
♪ Ah, that's just not the way

34:30.224 --> 34:32.025
What is that?

34:33.210 --> 34:34.583
Mm...

34:35.730 --> 34:37.731
I'm engaged!

34:38.569 --> 34:40.199
I-I was gonna tell you the other day,

34:40.234 --> 34:42.869
but, um, anyway, i-it just happened.

34:43.589 --> 34:45.192
[Sighs]

34:45.217 --> 34:46.652
Wow. That's...

34:46.677 --> 34:50.123
that is... that's r... That's
really great news, Joss.

34:50.143 --> 34:51.310
- Really?
- Yeah. [Chuckles]

34:51.344 --> 34:52.978
Absolutely, you're getting married.

34:53.013 --> 34:54.880
Yeah, I'm getting married.

34:59.417 --> 35:00.852
Good stuff.

35:10.195 --> 35:11.690
Got a second?

35:11.931 --> 35:14.100
We don't have to do this. You already won.

35:14.125 --> 35:16.126
You're the one who turned this into a game,

35:16.151 --> 35:18.384
which was a waste because
you're a damn good lawyer.

35:18.409 --> 35:20.342
<i>Was a damn good lawyer.</i>

35:20.367 --> 35:21.835
[Sniffs] You know, um...

35:21.860 --> 35:24.570
[Chuckles] You almost had me.

35:24.595 --> 35:26.264
I look out for myself.

35:26.289 --> 35:29.258
You grow up the way I did,
that's the way it works.

35:29.589 --> 35:31.224
I'm not gonna apologize for it.

35:31.469 --> 35:33.149
The fact that I got this far...

35:33.174 --> 35:34.798
No one ever thought it would happen.

35:34.823 --> 35:36.993
This far as a con artist
or this far as a lawyer?

35:37.018 --> 35:38.911
[Scoffs] Please. What's the difference?

35:38.936 --> 35:41.572
You know, when you first got here,

35:41.745 --> 35:43.245
I didn't like you.

35:43.827 --> 35:45.243
I figured you were a one-trick pony.

35:45.268 --> 35:46.568
And, to be honest, I didn't expect much,

35:46.593 --> 35:47.791
but you surprised me.

35:48.631 --> 35:51.712
You actually showed real talent.

35:51.858 --> 35:53.158
There was no doubt in my mind that

35:53.183 --> 35:55.217
you were gonna make partner...
no doubt in anybody's mind,

35:55.597 --> 35:57.178
except yours.

35:59.468 --> 36:01.937
How about you give me the
chance to prove you right?

36:01.962 --> 36:03.763
I know how much you like to be right.

36:03.788 --> 36:05.470
Ah...

36:05.495 --> 36:09.597
I'm afraid there's no chance
of you making partner here.

36:09.781 --> 36:11.226
[Clears throat]

36:11.942 --> 36:14.944
At least not for a good, long time.

36:16.630 --> 36:19.098
<i>So you're not firing me?</i>

36:19.828 --> 36:24.266
No, I've, uh, decided to keep
you on as a junior associate.

36:24.291 --> 36:26.072
Of course, you... you could always quit,

36:26.097 --> 36:28.632
but, I mean, the references
are gonna be a giant bitch.

36:29.020 --> 36:32.289
Why? Why would you do that?

36:33.301 --> 36:34.973
'Cause I'm the good guy.

36:35.350 --> 36:38.159
Also because Breitling
will only work with you,

36:38.184 --> 36:40.485
and I'm not about to lose
a $50 million account.

36:40.510 --> 36:43.011
So, look, keep your
head down, do your work,

36:43.036 --> 36:44.670
and stay away from Savi.

36:44.997 --> 36:47.031
She's gonna make partner.

36:48.343 --> 36:50.212
And she'll eat you alive.

36:52.931 --> 36:54.569
[Door closes]

36:56.164 --> 36:58.103
[Knock on door]

37:01.592 --> 37:03.727
- Savannah Davis?
- Yes. That's me.

37:09.105 --> 37:10.378
Thank you.

37:29.453 --> 37:31.588
[Cellphone ringing]

37:31.622 --> 37:34.060
♪ So I will run to you ♪

37:34.958 --> 37:37.500
♪ but you won't run from me ♪

37:37.961 --> 37:39.028
You got it?

37:39.063 --> 37:41.030
I most certainly did.

37:41.065 --> 37:43.407
I'm just a little confused as to why.

37:43.834 --> 37:45.634
Well, just consider it

37:45.669 --> 37:48.137
a thank you for the Chili Pepper tickets.

37:48.892 --> 37:51.473
But also, you... you kind
of turned my life around.

37:51.508 --> 37:52.641
I did?

37:52.676 --> 37:54.643
Well, don't sound so surprised.

37:54.678 --> 37:56.545
Well, I just... I am.

37:56.580 --> 37:58.314
I-I thought you were mad at me.

37:58.348 --> 38:00.782
Oh, my God, it is literally
the softest leather

38:00.817 --> 38:02.626
I have ever felt in my life.

38:02.994 --> 38:04.462
You spent too much.

38:04.487 --> 38:06.722
That's okay. I'm working now.

38:06.756 --> 38:07.756
You are?

38:07.790 --> 38:10.225
Oh, that's great. That's great. Where?

38:10.259 --> 38:12.060
Well, actually, it's kind of cool.

38:12.095 --> 38:13.729
I'd love to tell you about it over coffee,

38:13.763 --> 38:16.732
but... uh, oh, unless
your boyfriend would mind.

38:16.766 --> 38:18.166
Uh...

38:19.174 --> 38:21.502
I don't have a boyfriend anymore.

38:21.537 --> 38:22.970
We broke up.

38:23.864 --> 38:24.972
Oh.

38:25.006 --> 38:27.709
Then maybe I could tell you over dinner.

38:30.379 --> 38:34.014
So... Do I have to wait for dessert

38:34.049 --> 38:36.551
to find out how you feel about
my offer to move to Boston?

38:40.122 --> 38:44.759
I'm so sorry, but I can't go.

38:44.793 --> 38:48.162
But... You just said
you're quitting your job.

38:48.196 --> 38:50.128
You're totally free now.

38:50.698 --> 38:52.299
What's keeping you here?

38:52.333 --> 38:56.102
My life, Jacob. My friends.

38:56.883 --> 38:58.104
From what you told me,

38:58.139 --> 39:00.707
your friends are all moving
forward with their lives.

39:00.742 --> 39:03.377
You need to think about
yourself for a change.

39:03.411 --> 39:05.232
That's what I'm trying to do.

39:05.257 --> 39:07.758
<i>I need to figure out what I want now.</i>

39:08.048 --> 39:09.215
I don't know what that is,

39:09.250 --> 39:12.218
but I'm not ready to
pick up and move to a city

39:12.253 --> 39:13.719
where I don't know anyone.

39:13.754 --> 39:15.039
You'll know me.

39:15.064 --> 39:17.228
And you'll be busy with your new job

39:17.253 --> 39:20.869
and your new colleagues,
which is incredibly exciting,

39:20.894 --> 39:22.482
and I'm so proud of you.

39:22.997 --> 39:25.731
Don't you want someone
to spend your life with?

39:25.766 --> 39:28.032
Someone who will always be there for you?

39:29.269 --> 39:31.232
I have that.

39:31.772 --> 39:34.072
Savi, Joss, April.

39:34.107 --> 39:36.208
Hey. [Sighs] That's not the same.

39:37.444 --> 39:40.045
Friends can't fill all your needs, Karen.

39:40.079 --> 39:42.532
They're not just my friends.

39:43.750 --> 39:45.784
They're my family.

40:00.778 --> 40:03.580
[Voice breaking] Our timing
has always been a little off,

40:04.789 --> 40:06.246
hasn't it?

40:10.576 --> 40:17.581
♪ Giving this world
everything I've got ♪

40:18.984 --> 40:23.287
♪ Running through the woods
running through these shots ♪

40:23.322 --> 40:26.790
♪ Trying to survive a day ♪

40:26.825 --> 40:34.665
♪ and all I want is that
you extend your hand to me ♪

40:37.902 --> 40:39.932
You seem tense.

40:41.573 --> 40:44.541
Yeah. [Scoffs]

40:44.576 --> 40:45.809
Lots to do.

40:45.844 --> 40:48.432
You're not still mad at me, are you?

40:49.876 --> 40:51.047
Nope.

40:51.929 --> 40:53.049
No, we're good.

40:53.084 --> 40:55.385
♪ And hope for a better day ♪

40:55.419 --> 40:57.220
Oh, I think we're more than good.

40:57.255 --> 40:59.389
♪ You know those words you wrote me ♪

40:59.423 --> 41:04.294
In fact, I think the real
reason we were fighting

41:04.328 --> 41:07.060
was because of some...

41:07.498 --> 41:09.799
Underlying tension.

41:10.230 --> 41:15.004
♪ You're home ♪

41:15.038 --> 41:18.240
♪ you'll never be alone ♪

41:18.275 --> 41:20.342
♪ oh, yeah, yeah ♪

41:20.377 --> 41:24.513
♪ oh, yeah, oh, oh, yeah ♪

41:24.547 --> 41:27.816
♪ ooh-ooh-ooh,
ooh ♪

41:34.857 --> 41:36.858
[Sighs]

41:57.825 --> 41:59.465
Paul.

42:05.586 --> 42:07.087
[Knocking on door]

42:15.596 --> 42:17.164
Hi, Karen.

42:18.057 --> 42:19.829
Ben. Wh...

42:20.200 --> 42:21.400
How...

42:22.165 --> 42:24.136
I need to talk to you about something.

